===Etymology===
{{term|Afghan}} is believed by many modern Indic scholars to have been derived from a {{etyl|sa}} term {{term|Ashvakan||horseman|lang=sa}} though, some people claim its origin from the {{etyl|trk}} word {{term|Avagan||Original}} or else from  the {{etyl|la}} word {{term|Alban||mountaineers|lang-la}}; + {{etyl|fa}} suffix {{term|-stan||land|lang=fa}}. cf Persian {{term|فغانستان|sc=fa-Arab|tr=Afghanistan||land of Afghans}}

See: [[w:List of country name etymologies|Wikipedia article on Etymology of Afghanistan]]. Also see: [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan#Origin_and_history_of_the_name]

===Pronunciation===
